description.narrative: This activity (Social Protection Support) is a component of Social Protection Support Technical Cooperation reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Procurement of Services' and a budget of £421,003. This component benefits Mozambique, and works in the following sector(s): STD control including HIV/AIDS, Social Protection. , with the following implementing partners: Maxwell Stamp PLC, Overseas Development Institute, Oxford Policy Management, Palladium International Ltd (UK), School of Oriental and African Studies (SOAS), University of Manchester, The. The start date is 01-07-2008 and the end date is 31-03-2021.
